definition: Compound having a fully conjugated cyclic dione structure derived from aromatic compounds by conversion of an even number of ‒CH= groups into ‒C(=O)‒ groups with any necessary rearrangement of double bonds
selection_criteria: it has a fully conjugated cyclic dione structure
it is derived from aromatic compounds
it is derived by conversion of an even number of ‒CH= groups into ‒C(=O)‒ groups with any necessary rearrangement of double bonds
